 ConsumerLoop;config;consumer;start;last_consumed;cr
 ⍝ Consumer consumes messages from two topics synchronously

 #.Init'.'

⍝ consumer configurations
 config←0 2⍴⍬
 config⍪←'bootstrap.servers' 'localhost:9092'
 config⍪←'client.id' 'consumerLclient'
 config⍪←'group.id' 'consumerLgroup'
 config⍪←'auto.offset.reset' 'earliest'
 ⎕←'consumer configuration'
 config

⍝ Init consumer
 consumer←⎕NEW #.Consumer config

⍝ Subscribe consumer to topic
 ⎕←'Subscribe consumer on topic: topic1 and topic2'
 consumer.subscribe'topic1' 'topic2'
 ⎕←'Waiting for rebalance before starting consuming...'
 ⎕DL 5

 ⎕←'Start polling messages'
 start←3⊃⎕AI
 last_consumed←3⊃⎕AI
 :While 60000>(3⊃⎕AI)-last_consumed ⍝ Stop listening when not consuming for more than one minute
     cr←consumer.consume_record
     :If 1=⊃cr
     :AndIf 20000>(3⊃⎕AI)-start
         :Continue
     :ElseIf 0=⊃cr
         (2⊃cr).(Topic Payload Key Partition)
         last_consumed←3⊃⎕AI
         start←0
     :EndIf
 :EndWhile
 ⎕←'Have not received messages in 60 seconds... Stop waiting.'
 ⎕EX'consumer'
